  "issue_title": "With `invoke_without_command` set, commands are not marked as optional",
  "issue_body": "Having\n\n```python\n@click.group(invoke_without_command=True)\ndef main():\n    if ctx.invoked_subcommand is not None:\n        return\n    # do something by default\n```\n\nI expect `--help` to output:\n\n```\nUsage: app.py [OPTIONS] [COMMAND] [ARGS]...\n```\n\nBut it outputs:\n\n```\nUsage: app.py [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]...\n```\n\nEnvironment:\n\n- Python version: 3.11.8\n- Click version: 8.2.0\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-27T16:23:34Z",
